1️⃣ Locator Fallback Engine (UI Self‑Healing)
This is the easiest and most impactful.

How it works
Each element has:

Primary locator

Secondary locator(s)

Heuristic locator(s) (text, role, partial match, etc.)

Example structure
java
public class SmartLocator {
    private String primary;
    private List<String> fallbacks;
}
Healing logic
When Playwright fails to find the primary locator:

Try fallback locators

Try heuristic locators

Log which locator succeeded

Store the successful locator in a local DB/JSON

Use the healed locator next time

Why it works
Most UI failures are caused by:

Minor DOM changes

Attribute renaming

CSS refactoring

Fallbacks solve 80% of these instantly.

