Code
expected: "userId"
actual:   "user_id"
You can auto‑heal using:

Levenshtein distance

Underscore removal

Case normalization

This solves most API contract drift issues.

4️⃣ Retry With Context Awareness
Instead of blind retries, use smart retries:

Example:
If a click fails → try scrollIntoView → retry

If a network call fails → retry with exponential backoff

If a page load fails → reload page → retry

If a locator fails → try fallback locators

This is extremely effective and easy to implement.

5️⃣ Self‑Healing Knowledge Store
This is the “memory” of your healing system.

Store:

Successful fallback locators

API field mappings

